      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Haiku himself is small, but ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Haiku, the Robot",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " as a game really punches above its weight. OK it doesn’t look particularly high-def or glamorous, but it plays like any good Metroidvania should.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There are other better looking Metroidvanias out there which aren’t as fun as Haiku, the Robot, so my recommendation to my fellow Metroidvania lovers is to go out and buy this game, while supporting a solo developer whose dream was to make a game one day!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
